                        <pf>Rev.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Smith</ln>
                        <fn>Geritt</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Article details how different denominations discussed the irrepressible
                    conflict between freedom and slavery.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>6</column>
                <head>"Harpers Ferry" in a Tract Society</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Cochran</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Rev. Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Schlosser</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Rev. Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Tappan</ln>
                        <fn>Lewis</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Brown</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>A number of fanatical clergymen have gathered in Chicago to discuss
                    Seward's irrepressible conflict between North and South, including John Brown's
                    insurrection.</summary>
            </div>
