                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Nesbitt</ln>
                        <fn>S. James</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Letter from S. James Nesbitt to the Vindicator tells about how Nesbitt
                    talked with a man from the area of Harper's Ferry who told the story of a
                    contractor who absconded without paying his workers. These workers may have
                    joined the rebellion in Harper's Ferry. Nesbitt responded that he would be angry
                    too but not angry enough to join Abolitionists in inciting rebellion.</summary>
            </div>
